

Currently i am working on developing Auto Switch algorithm on buds. 
Samsung is launching a new product where buds are worn like earrings. So they are reversable. 
I am developing that algorithm. After wear on is detected. We take accel values at 20 ms for 400 ms. 
Ie total 20 values. We find the max and min value by magnitude. We use a low pass filer on our values. 
We find the mean our values in this period. And put threashold checks on it. 

Before this i have developed proximity sensor algorithm for wear on detection. 
Samsung inherently used skin sensor for ear detection. 
I was tasked to make an algorithm using proximity sensor.
In that we take sensor data from proximity sensor. It gives a raw number value. 
But the main problem was deciding the reference value. 
Because the open air values of proximity sensor changes with height and pressure. 
So we decided to do calibration once at factory level(fallback value) and once at user level. 
Using data estimates, we computed that inEar values are usually 2000 more than open air raw values. 
And open air raw values are computed using calibration. 
We also used accel sensor to detect no move table condition as on table accel is stable and variance is is very low. 
So if the variance is in particular low range we detect table and turn on the buds.

